  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For because ye did it not at the first,.... Did not sanctify themselves, as the supplement in our version directs; but rather the sense is, ye were not there at first, when the ark was brought from Kirjathjearim as far as the house of Obededom, as they should have been; they were not then employed, as was their business, and therefore ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the Lord our God made a breach upon us; by smiting Uzzah with death, who was no Levite, and touched the ark, which is called his \"error\", and for which God smote him, 2 Samuel 6:7 on which place Lud. Capellus observes, the word \"shal\", we there render \"error\", signifies a \"disease\" in the Arabic language, and might formerly design a sudden one with the Hebrew; as an apoplexy; and so the sense be, that God smote Uzzah with an apoplexy, of which he suddenly died: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "the Lord our God made a breach upon us; by smiting Uzzah with death, who was no Levite, and touched the ark, which is called his \"error\", and for which God smote him, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 6:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " on which place Lud. Capellus observes, the word \"shal\", we there render \"error\", signifies a \"disease\" in the Arabic language, and might formerly design a sudden one with the Hebrew; as an apoplexy; and so the sense be, that God smote Uzzah with an apoplexy, of which he suddenly died: ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for that we sought him not after the due order; but, instead of employing the Levites to carry the ark on their shoulders, it was put upon a cart. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "for that we sought him not after the due order; but, instead of employing the Levites to carry the ark on their shoulders, it was put upon a cart. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
